<i>They keep taking from me,
and it’s driving me mad</i>
{\ O (spread): Go to that guy}

218
00:13:42,426 --> 00:13:50,568
<i>This place reeks of all these deadbeats</i>

219
00:13:50,568 --> 00:13:58,710
<i>I might already be in hell,
the way it makes me sick</i>

220
00:13:58,710 --> 00:14:06,852
<i>And yet, my mum told me to be noble</i>

221
00:14:06,852 --> 00:14:15,000
<i>She held me and taught me to be proud</i>

222
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:19,000
<i>“Hey Dio, look up at the stars”</i>

223
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:24,600
<i>She kept on saying that,
until the illness took her</i>
{\ O (spread): Are you acting like a father now?}

224
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:30,200
Just like that...
{\ O (spread): Listen, Dio}

225
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:35,800
<i>Why are my hands always empty?</i>
{\ O (spread): You are smart.}

226
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:41,400
<i>Am I just here to be taken from?</i>

227
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:47,000
<i>Tell me, Joestar, the sky
that you have over you</i>

228
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:52,000
<i>Is it blue?</i>

229
00:14:52,000 --> 00:15:00,666
<i>Tell me, Joestar</i>

230
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:09,332
<i>This disgraceful father of
mine, the lowest of the low</i>

231
00:15:09,332 --> 00:15:18,000
<i>A deadbeat will always be a deadbeat</i>

232
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:29,000
<i>Under this murky sky,</i>

233
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:33,333
<i>He struggled and struggled,
and this is how he’s gonna die</i>

234
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:37,666
<i>Now, I’ll go take this “inheritance”</i>

235
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:42,000
<i>I’ll use any means, yes,
to set me on my path</i>

236
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:56,000
<i>I may have nothing in my hands yet,</i>

237
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:01,000
<i>That means I’ll start from here</i>

238
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:06,000
<i>Tell me, Joestar, in the sky over you,</i>

239
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:11,000
<i>Is the sun shining?</i>

240
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:17,000
<i>It is, isn’t it, Joestar?</i>

241
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:23,400
Oh yeah!

242
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:29,800
You’ve got something good today too, eh?
{\ O (spread): Look up at the stars}

243
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:36,200
Give it back!

244
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:42,600
Over here!

245
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:49,000
Hey Erina, I heard that
your old man’s a quack!

246
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,000
My father’s a real doctor!

247
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:55,000
Oh really? This hat looks expensive!

248
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:59,000
Stop it! It was a birthday
present from my mother!

249
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:03,000
Stop right there!

250
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,000
What are you doing?! Take this!
{\ O (rank): Is that sky blue?}

251
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:11,000
I hate when guys try to
act cool in front of girls!
{\ O (spread): Nacho Star}

252
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:17,000
Ow! That hurt!
{\ O (spread): Ugly, terrible father, loser, always a loser}

253
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,000
-Hey, do you know who this guy is?
{\ O (rank): Under this murky sky, I continued to struggle and die}

254
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:32,000
If he’s that Jonathan kid
from the Joestar family,
{\ O (gap): Let's receive our inheritance now, it's all from our parents, let's go on a journey}

255
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,000
I’m gonna give him even
more of a walloping!
{\ O (spread): I still have nothing in my hands, so let's start from here}

256
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,000
Ah-ha!
{\ O (spread): Joestar, you have the sun in the sky}

257
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
He <i>is</i> the Joestars’ Jonathan!
{\ O (spread): That's right, Joestar}

258
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Snotty little rich boy! You think
you’re so high and mighty?

259
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Danny!
{\ O (spread): Your father is a good doctor}

260
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Eh?!
{\ O (spread): What do you think?}

261
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:53,000
Let’s go already! Shit!
{\ O (spread): But it's an expensive hat}

262
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,000
Uh... Are you alright?
{\ O (gap): Stop it, your mother gave it to you for your birthday.}

263
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Leave me alone!

264
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,000
But...
{\ O (rank): What are you doing?}

265
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,000
I did this because I wanted to.
{\ O (gap): Just because you're in front of a girl, you're trying to act cool}

266
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:04,000
I didn’t do it to get you to thank me.
{\ O (spread): Hey, do you know who this is?}

267
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:07,000
My goal is to become a true gentleman.

268
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:10,000
You were a damsel in distress,
so I had to stand up for you.
{\ O (spread): After all, this guy is Jona of the Joestar family.}

269
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,000
I’ll beat them, someday.

270
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,000
Let’s go, Danny!

271
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:22,000
Oh, wait!

272
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,000
Jonathan Joestar...
{\ O (rank): Um, are you okay?}

273
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,000
You...
{\ O (rank): Leave me alone}

274
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:12,000
You must be Dio Brando!
{\ O (rank): but}

275
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:12,000
And you’re...
{\ O (spread): I did it because I wanted to, not to be thanked by you.}

276
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Jonathan Joestar?
{\ O (gap): I'm aiming for true sincerity. You were a girl and I was having trouble with you, so I just stood up to you.}

277
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,000
Everyone calls me JoJo. Nice to meet you!
{\ O (gap): Someday I'll be able to win}

278
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,333
Ah, Danny! I’ll introduce you.
{\ O (spread): Okay, let's go}

279
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:24,666
This is my friend, Danny.
He’s a clever old hound!
{\ O (spread): Jonathan Joestar}

280
00:19:24,666 --> 00:19:28,000
Oh, and don’t worry about him biting!

281
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Friend?

282
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,000
Yeah!
{\ O (spread): you}

283
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,000
Danny! What was that for!
{\ O (spread): You're Dio Brando!}

284
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,000
Danny!
{\ O (rank): So you're Jonathan Joestar?}

285
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:39,000
You won’t get away with this!
{\ O (spread): Everyone calls me Chocho!}

286
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,000
We’ve been waiting for you, Dio Brando.
{\ O (gap): Looking forward to working with you.}

287
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,000
Lord Joestar!
{\ O (gap): Let me introduce you to my friend Danny.}

288
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:48,000
Come inside!
{\ O (spread): It's a very useful shape.}

289
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,000
From today on, you’ll be
living here in our mansion.

290
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
Something wrong, JoJo?
{\ O (spread): friend?}

291
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,000
Ah, nothing.

292
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
You’ve travelled all the way from
London, Dio. You must be tired.
{\ O (gap): What are you doing? I won't forgive you!}

293
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,586
Starting today, you are part of our family.
{\ O (spread): I've been waiting for you, Diobrando.}

294
00:20:02,586 --> 00:20:05,172
You’ll be given the same
kind of life as my son, JoJo.

295
00:20:05,172 --> 00:20:07,760
Yes!
{\ O (spread): Come in. This is the mansion where you will be living from today onwards.}

296
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:11,000
I am grateful for your
kindness, Lord Joestar.
{\ O (gap): What's up, JoJo?}

297
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,540
Mister Brando!
{\ O (spread): You must be tired from traveling all the way from London, Dio.}

298
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:16,540
I’m Police Inspector Archer!
{\ O (gap): From today onwards, you are part of our family. Please live your life just like our son, Jojo.}

299
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:18,760
Police? Has something happened?
{\ O (rank): Yes, I am grateful for Lord Joestar's actions.}

300
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:21,440
Oh, no!
{\ O (spread): Hehehehe.}

301
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:24,120
I’m an old friend of the Joestars.
{\ O (spread): Brand, this is Inspector Archer.}

302
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:26,800
Although, I could hear Danny
whimper a moment ago...
{\ O (spread): Police? Did something happen?}

303
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,480
Ah, that was—

304
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:32,160
-He came at me so suddenly.

305
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:34,840
When I jumped in surprise,
I think my leg may have hit him!

306
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:37,520
Danny is the Joestar household’s
wonderful guard dog.

307
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:43,760
He’s a friendly creature, but
I’m sorry he surprised you.
{\ O (rank): He's quite friendly, but it seems he startled you.}

308
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,660
JoJo!
{\ O (spread): JoJo, enough about Danny.}

309
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:47,560
You’ll let this Danny matter go, right?
{\ O (spread): yes.}

310
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:49,460
Yes, sir.
{\ O (spread): Jojo has also lost his mother, and they are the same age.}

311
00:20:49,460 --> 00:20:51,360
Good.
{\ O (spread): Please get along well with each other.}

312
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:56,320
JoJo has lost his mother too—
and you both are the same age!
{\ O (rank): Now, let me show you to your room.}

313
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:59,300
Make sure to get along with each other.
{\ O (rank): Mr. Brand.}

314
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:02,320
Now, allow me to show you to your room.

315
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:05,240
Mister Brando!
{\ O (rank): nice to meet you!}

316
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,160
Nice to have met you!

317
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:14,240
Ta-ta, JoJo!

318
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:19,320
Now then, let me get—

319
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:24,400
Watch it!

320
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,120
Don’t touch my bag!

321
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:27,420
I was just trying to carry it for—
{\ O (rank): Don't touch my bag.}

322
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:29,320
That’s enough.
{\ O (spread): I'll try to carry it}

323
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:32,020
Your hand is covered in dog drool.
{\ O (gap): 結構}

324
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:35,970
Pardon me if I don’t want
it all over my things!
{\ O (spread): Your hands are sticky with dog drool}

325
00:21:35,970 --> 00:21:39,920
Alright JoJo, I’ll tell
you from the get-go.

326
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:43,870
I like being the best!
I’m always number one!

327
00:21:43,870 --> 00:21:47,820
I don’t care who you are,
no one looks down on me!

328
00:21:47,820 --> 00:21:49,820
I was only trying to be friendly!

329
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:52,320
What are you two doing?

330
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,120
And one more thing—

331
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,120
I hate dogs.
{\ O (rank): I just try to be friendly}

332
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:13,120
The way they grovel and suck
up to humans disgusts me.
{\ O (spread): What are you both doing?}

333
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:24,120
Keep your stupid dog away from me!
{\ O (spread): One more thing}

334
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:35,120
Coming, Lord Joestar!
{\ O (spread): I hate dogs}

335
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:46,120
Thus, with this meeting, the
two boys’ youth had begun.

336
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,120
Are you coming, JoJo, Dio?

337
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:50,977
<i>Bear in mind, as honourable nobles,</i>

338
00:22:50,977 --> 00:22:54,834
<i>We take on the duty of
becoming true gentlemen</i>

339
00:22:54,834 --> 00:22:58,691
<i>This is why we study, acquire knowledge,</i>

340
00:22:58,691 --> 00:23:02,548
{\an8}<i>(Without pause!)</i>

341
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:06,405
{\an8}<i>(Without limit!)</i>

342
00:23:06,405 --> 00:23:10,262
<i>And arm ourselves with logic!</i>

343
00:23:10,262 --> 00:23:14,120
{\an8}<i>(So you’ll never lose!)</i>

344
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:16,120
<i>Under the guidance of
the goddess of familial love</i>
{\ O (rank): Here comes JoJo}

345
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:19,620
<i>For the sake of heading
the house of Joestar</i>

346
00:23:19,620 --> 00:23:23,120
{\an8}<i>(The honourable Joestars!)</i>

347
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:26,620
<i>What’s this, JoJo? JoJo!</i>

348
00:23:26,620 --> 00:23:30,120
<i>The same mistakes once again</i>

349
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:31,120
<i>How many times have
you made them! Six times!</i>

350
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:38,120
<i>Dio has all of them correct!</i>

351
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:42,342
It’s just because I love reading so much!

352
00:23:42,342 --> 00:23:46,564
But they haven’t even
taught us this in school yet!

353
00:23:46,564 --> 00:23:50,786
<i>Bear in mind, as proud nobles,</i>

354
00:23:50,786 --> 00:23:55,008
<i>We behave like true gentlemen</i>

355
00:23:55,008 --> 00:23:59,230
<i>Sit up straight, use your knife with grace,</i>

356
00:23:59,230 --> 00:24:03,452
{\an8}<i>(So elegantly!)</i>

357
00:24:03,452 --> 00:24:07,674
{\an8}<i>(So gracefully!)</i>

358
00:24:07,674 --> 00:24:11,896
<i>So that your mouth always remains spotless</i>

359
00:24:11,896 --> 00:24:16,120
{\an8}<i>(Unfailingly!)</i>
{\ O (spread): Under the Goddess of Self-Love}

360
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:18,120
<i>Under the guidance of
the goddess of familial love</i>

361
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:22,120
<i>For the sake of being loved as a Joestar!</i>

362
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:26,120
{\an8}<i>(The proud Joestars!)</i>

363
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:30,120
<i>What’s this, JoJo? JoJo!</i>

364
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:34,120
<i>Do you call yourself a gentleman?</i>

365
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:38,120
<i>Look at Dio’s elegant touch</i>

366
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:42,120
<i>His manners are perfect!</i>

367
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:46,120
<i>Take away JoJo’s plates!
You will go without dinner tonight!</i>
{\ O (spread): How many times has this happened?}

368
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,120
<i>Observe and follow Dio’s example</i>

369
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:53,590
<i>I am embarrassed by
how much I’ve spoiled you</i>
{\ O (spread): All uses are correct}

370
00:24:53,590 --> 00:25:00,060
But...

371
00:25:00,060 --> 00:25:06,530
My mother taught me well. She
always made sure I sat up straight.

372
00:25:06,530 --> 00:25:13,000
<i>Bear in mind, as honourable nobles,</i>

373
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:23,000
<i>In our hearts we must always consider
questions of philosophy and justice</i>

374
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:28,000
In our great England, a tale of two knights
has been passed down for generations.

375
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:33,000
One day, their master was
taken prisoner by the enemy.

376
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:41,000
The enemy was afraid of the
two knights, who had great power.

377
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,000
And so she gave them this condition:

378
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:49,000
“If you two will be executed in her place,
I will guarantee the life of your master.”

379
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:52,000
Here is my question for you:

380
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:55,000
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

381
00:25:55,000 --> 00:26:02,000
Those two knights who gave themselves
up as prisoners to save their master;

382
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:06,000
What was the first thing they
saw through their prison bars?

383
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:10,000
Was it the mud that lay before their eyes?

384
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:15,000
Or was it the stars shining above them?

385
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,000
What do you think?

386
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:18,555
The stars?

387
00:26:18,555 --> 00:26:19,110
Or the mud?
{\ O (spread): Under the Goddess of Self-Love}

388
00:26:19,110 --> 00:26:19,665
I...

389
00:26:19,665 --> 00:26:20,220
I think they were looking at the mud.

390
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:20,775
What’s your reasoning?

391
00:26:20,775 --> 00:26:21,330
In the end, they had no choice
but to die for their master.

392
00:26:21,330 --> 00:26:21,885
You can’t achieve anything if you’re dead.

393
00:26:21,885 --> 00:26:22,440
So no matter what tricks
they would have had to pull,

394
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:23,000
I think they should have stayed
alive and done something!

395
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:30,000
I think...

396
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,000
They were looking at the stars!

397
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,750
They held onto their honour!

398
00:26:53,750 --> 00:26:56,500
The names of those two knights
will be etched into history!

399
00:26:56,500 --> 00:26:59,250
So what!

400
00:26:59,250 --> 00:27:02,000
So what?

401
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:05,000
The way one lives, and the things
one does, those are important!

402
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,000
But they—

403
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,000
They were left empty-handed
in the end!
{\ O (spread): Follow their example}

404
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Such regret...

405
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:15,000
Such powerlessness...

406
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,000
What they saw was the mud!

407
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,666
Their lesson is to teach us what
we can achieve by staying alive!

408
00:27:20,666 --> 00:27:23,332
They held onto their
pride until the very end!

409
00:27:23,332 --> 00:27:25,998
They were looking at the stars! I think
they’re teaching us <i>how</i> we should live!

410
00:27:25,998 --> 00:27:28,664
Listen!

411
00:27:28,664 --> 00:27:31,330
You’re a noble! You have it all!

412
00:27:31,330 --> 00:27:34,000
You’ve lived by taking
from those beneath you!
{\ O (spread): Always question philosophy and truth in your mind}

413
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:38,000
So isn’t it your responsibility to think
about what you’ll achieve with your life?
{\ O (gap): There are two knights in English folklore.}

414
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,000
I—
{\ O (rank): One day, their master was taken prisoner by the enemy.}

415
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:41,000
That’s enough, you two.
{\ O (spread): The enemy feared the two knights' great power and made a condition.}

416
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:46,000
There’s no right answer to this question.
{\ O (rank): If you are executed in his place, the Lord's life will be guaranteed.}

417
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:50,761
Bear in mind—
{\ O (spread): Here's the problem for both of you}

418
00:27:50,761 --> 00:27:55,522
<i>All people live in a prison called fate</i>
{\ O (spread): yes}

419
00:27:55,522 --> 00:28:00,283
<i>Reaching out through those bars,</i>
{\ O (spread): Two knights sacrificed themselves to save their master and were taken prisoner.}

420
00:28:00,283 --> 00:28:05,044
<i>Do they see the stars? Or the mud?</i>
{\ O (spread): Is what you see beyond the prison bars the mud in front of you?}

421
00:28:05,044 --> 00:28:09,805
<i>Either one could be said to be correct</i>
{\ O (spread): Or is it the star shining above?}

422
00:28:09,805 --> 00:28:14,566
<i>A world without disparity, that’s sports</i>
{\ O (spread): Which do you think?}

423
00:28:14,566 --> 00:28:19,327
<i>Where courage alone
