01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:44,000
<i>(Light up the darkness with
your unwavering heart!)</i>

1029
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:49,846
<i>Your refreshing sunlight</i>

1030
01:09:49,846 --> 01:09:55,692
<i>Brought me completely to my knees</i>

1031
01:09:55,692 --> 01:10:01,538
<i>This must be some
strange twist of fate!</i>

1032
01:10:01,538 --> 01:10:07,384
<i>Let’s toast—to our meeting!</i>

1033
01:10:07,384 --> 01:10:13,230
JoJo...

1034
01:10:13,230 --> 01:10:19,076
JoJo...!

1035
01:10:19,076 --> 01:10:24,922
<i>Dio...</i>

1036
01:10:24,922 --> 01:10:30,768
JoJo has gone off to London...

1037
01:10:30,768 --> 01:10:36,614
Could he have died a dog’s death already?

1038
01:10:36,614 --> 01:10:42,460
<i>Dio...</i>

1039
01:10:42,460 --> 01:10:48,306
Or could he have found
evidence of the medicine?

1040
01:10:48,306 --> 01:10:54,152
Which is it?!

1041
01:10:54,152 --> 01:11:00,000
<i>Dio...</i>

1042
01:11:00,000 --> 01:11:04,000
Booze! I can’t help but drink!

1043
01:11:04,000 --> 01:11:09,000
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>
{\ O (rank): I came here for my father.}

1044
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:11,000
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>
{\ O (rank): That's why Kelsion thought you must have a father, mother, and siblings.}

1045
01:11:11,000 --> 01:11:13,000
-Shut up, get out of my head!

1046
01:11:13,000 --> 01:11:18,000
<i>You’re the only one I care about</i>

1047
01:11:18,000 --> 01:11:20,000
<i>Become the richest man!</i>

1048
01:11:20,000 --> 01:11:22,500
-You piece of shit, we’re not the same!

1049
01:11:22,500 --> 01:11:25,000
Watch where you’re going, twat!
{\ O (spread): That's why Kelsion doesn't want to do anything that would cause your father grief.}

1050
01:11:25,000 --> 01:11:27,000
Oi, are you listening, you stupid brat?
{\ O (rank): Tell me your name.}

1051
01:11:27,000 --> 01:11:27,133
You should ask yer mum to hold
you by the hand next time!
{\ O (spread): Jora, Joestar.}

1052
01:11:27,133 --> 01:11:27,266
{\an8}<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>
{\ O (spread): Joestar-san, please name the person playing the German role.}

1053
01:11:27,266 --> 01:11:27,399
Didn’t you hear me?
{\ O (spread): Be careful. They're tricky. Hey, treat your wounds.}

1054
01:11:27,399 --> 01:11:27,532
Oi! You piece of shit—
{\ O (spread): This Speed ​​Burgon will guide you to Minsei.}

1055
01:11:27,532 --> 01:11:27,665
{\an8}<i>Are you stupid? Oi, Dio!</i>
{\ O (spread): Why?}

1056
01:11:27,665 --> 01:11:27,798
{\an8}<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>
{\ O (spread): I like you.}

1057
01:11:27,798 --> 01:11:27,931
You filthy old tramps with
no sense of personal hygiene...
{\ O (spread): Foca Street}

1058
01:11:27,931 --> 01:11:28,064
{\an8}<i>Are you stupid? Oi, Dio!</i>
{\ O (spread): O man of resolve,}

1059
01:11:28,064 --> 01:11:28,197
How dare you! You bastard!
{\ O (spread): Foca Street}

1060
01:11:28,197 --> 01:11:28,330
What did you do to my mate?!
{\ O (spread): Continue taking a look}

1061
01:11:28,330 --> 01:11:28,463
{\an8}<i>One man’s misfortune...</i>
{\ O (spread): You who see the stars in your heart}

1062
01:11:28,463 --> 01:11:28,596
I’ll kill you!

1063
01:11:28,596 --> 01:11:28,729
{\an8}<i>Is another man’s fortune!</i>

1064
01:11:28,729 --> 01:11:28,862
Interesting, this is a good
opportunity to try it out!
{\ O (spread): Light up the darkness}

1065
01:11:28,862 --> 01:11:29,000
{\an8}<i>You’re my clever boy!</i>

1066
01:11:29,000 --> 01:11:31,000
What’re you mumbling about?!

1067
01:12:02,000 --> 01:12:04,000
It’s a live human experiment!

1068
01:12:04,000 --> 01:12:09,000
{\an8}<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

1069
01:12:09,000 --> 01:12:11,000
JoJo!

1070
01:12:11,000 --> 01:12:17,500
I’ll find the answer to your
research myself right now!

1071
01:12:17,500 --> 01:12:24,000
{\an8}<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

1072
01:12:24,000 --> 01:12:26,000
What...

1073
01:12:26,000 --> 01:12:28,000
What—

1074
01:12:28,000 --> 01:12:28,000
{\an8}<i>[AZTEC CHANTING]</i>

1075
01:12:28,000 --> 01:12:30,000
What is this light?

1076
01:12:33,000 --> 01:12:35,000
Was I hallucinating?

1077
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:39,000
He’s dead...

1078
01:12:39,000 --> 01:12:42,500
The spikes pierced so deep into his skull,
it must have killed him instantly.

1079
01:12:42,500 --> 01:12:46,000
This mask is just some ancient
sacrificial torture device.
{\ O (spread): I can't help but drink alcohol}

1080
01:12:46,000 --> 01:12:48,000
He’s not dead!
{\ O (rank): Can't you hear my voice?}

1081
01:12:50,000 --> 01:12:53,000
Fangs?! What is he?!
{\ O (rank): A voice calling you}

1082
01:12:53,000 --> 01:13:01,250
<i>I’m thirsty, thirsty, so thirsty!</i>
{\ O (spread): Shut up and don't come out}

1083
01:13:01,250 --> 01:13:09,500
He’s sucking my blood!
{\ O (spread): You are the only one who can see the sun}

1084
01:13:09,500 --> 01:13:17,750
His face is...
{\ O (spread): Become the richest}

1085
01:13:17,750 --> 01:13:26,000
Becoming younger?!
{\ O (spread): The case is different between you and me}

1086
01:13:26,000 --> 01:13:31,860
I don’t want the morning sun
to be the last thing I ever see!
{\ O (gap): Where am I looking, Tanchiki?}

1087
01:13:31,860 --> 01:13:43,930
I was saved...
{\ O (spread): Nyahaha are you listening to this?}

1088
01:13:43,930 --> 01:13:56,000
By the sunlight...

1089
01:13:56,000 --> 01:14:05,000
He turned into ash...
{\ O (rank): When you go out,}

1090
01:14:05,000 --> 01:14:14,500
Ow!

1091
01:14:14,500 --> 01:14:24,000
So this...

1092
01:14:24,000 --> 01:14:26,000
Is the power of the Stone Mask.

1093
01:14:26,000 --> 01:14:29,333
So, where is Dio?

1094
01:14:29,333 --> 01:14:32,666
It seems he hasn’t come
home since last night.

1095
01:14:32,666 --> 01:14:36,000
I’ll call for reinforcements right away.

1096
01:14:36,000 --> 01:14:37,000
Please use the foyer.

1097
01:14:37,000 --> 01:14:38,000
Thank you.

1098
01:14:38,000 --> 01:14:40,000
-You there!
-Sir!

1099
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:42,000
This Asian fellow,
Wang Chan—take him away.

1100
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:43,000
Yes sir!

1101
01:14:43,000 --> 01:14:46,333
Oi, come on!

1102
01:14:46,333 --> 01:14:49,666
JoJo...

1103
01:14:49,666 --> 01:14:53,000
I apologise.
{\ O (spread): Human experimentation}

1104
01:14:53,000 --> 01:14:55,000
This is my cross to bear.
{\ O (rank): JoeJoe}

1105
01:14:55,000 --> 01:14:55,066
What?
{\ O (spread): I'll solve your research}

1106
01:14:55,066 --> 01:14:55,132
If only I had made sure
that man was exiled...
{\ O (spread): What}

1107
01:14:55,132 --> 01:14:55,198
Dio’s father...
{\ O (spread): What}

1108
01:14:55,198 --> 01:14:55,264
Dario Brando.

1109
01:14:55,264 --> 01:14:55,330
What do you mean?
{\ O (spread): Hallucination?}

1110
01:14:55,330 --> 01:14:55,396
I’ll tell you about it.
{\ O (spread): Dead}

1111
01:14:55,396 --> 01:14:55,462
This happened when you were a baby.
{\ O (spread): If you get stabbed in the head with this much force, it's only natural that you'll die instantly.}

1112
01:14:55,462 --> 01:14:55,528
This is certainly my ring,
{\ O (spread): It's an ancient instrument of torture and murder.}

1113
01:14:55,528 --> 01:14:55,594
But I never reported a theft.
{\ O (spread): Not dead}

1114
01:14:55,594 --> 01:14:55,660
I arrested the man who
was caught pawning it.
{\ O (spread): Hiba, what is this guy?}

1115
01:14:55,660 --> 01:14:55,726
Lord Joestar had that ring specially made
as a pair for his and his wife’s engagement.

1116
01:14:55,726 --> 01:14:55,792
It was obvious that it was stolen!

1117
01:14:55,792 --> 01:14:55,858
Yes, it’s the ring I had made with my wife.

1118
01:14:55,858 --> 01:14:55,924
When Lord Joestar thought about his wife,

1119
01:14:55,924 --> 01:14:56,000
Tears welled up in his eyes.

1120
01:14:56,000 --> 01:14:57,000
I...
{\ O (rank): I hate that the sun I see is the last one I see!}

1121
01:14:57,000 --> 01:14:57,660
I arrested the criminal!
{\ O (spread): Thank goodness...}

1122
01:14:57,660 --> 01:14:58,320
Would you like to see for yourself?
{\ O (spread): Did the sunlight turn it to ash?}

1123
01:14:58,320 --> 01:14:58,980
Stealing from a noble is a heavy offence.

1124
01:14:58,980 --> 01:14:59,640
He’s certain to be exiled!

1125
01:14:59,640 --> 01:15:00,300
I see.

1126
01:15:00,300 --> 01:15:00,960
Here he is! Oi! Wake up! Brando!

1127
01:15:00,960 --> 01:15:01,620
Brando?!

1128
01:15:01,620 --> 01:15:02,280
Oh, bollocks.

1129
01:15:02,280 --> 01:15:02,940
Then that means—
{\ O (spread): The power of the Stone Mask...}

1130
01:15:02,940 --> 01:15:03,600
Dario Brando isn’t some saviour,
{\ O (spread): So Dio...}

1131
01:15:03,600 --> 01:15:04,260
But a thief!
{\ O (spread): He hasn't returned from the liquor store yet.}

1132
01:15:04,260 --> 01:15:04,920
Even knowing this,
Lord Joestar adopted Dio.
{\ O (spread): Quickly chase after them...}

1133
01:15:04,920 --> 01:15:05,580
Why?
{\ O (spread): Please use the room}

1134
01:15:05,580 --> 01:15:06,240
I...
{\ O (spread): thank you}

1135
01:15:06,240 --> 01:15:06,900
I was moved to tears by
what Lord Joestar said next.
{\ O (spread): Hey!}

1136
01:15:06,900 --> 01:15:09,500
Did he tell you...
{\ O (gap): Ah...}

1137
01:15:09,500 --> 01:16:40,900
That I gave him this ring?

1138
01:16:40,900 --> 01:16:41,700
Yes, he said that. A lie!
{\ O (rank): yes!}

1139
01:16:42,900 --> 01:16:43,800
It’s not a lie.
{\ O (gap): Hahahaha...}

1140
01:16:45,500 --> 01:16:48,100
This is what I gave him.
{\ O (gap): Hahahaha...}

1141
01:16:49,400 --> 01:16:50,500
He is innocent.
{\ O (gap): long…}

1142
01:16:50,700 --> 01:16:52,300
But it’s a memento of your wife!

1143
01:16:52,700 --> 01:16:53,400
Mr. Brando,
{\ O (rank): This is my fault...}

1144
01:16:54,400 --> 01:16:55,800
This is yours.

1145
01:16:56,800 --> 01:17:01,100
With this ring, please buy
what you need for your family.
{\ O (rank): I…}

1146
01:17:01,100 --> 01:17:03,700
Lord Joestar! Are you taking the piss?!

1147
01:17:04,200 --> 01:17:15,200
<i>If I were suffering from poverty</i>

1148
01:17:17,200 --> 01:17:20,700
<i>I would have done the same
thing, yes, for the ones I love</i>

1149
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:37,700
<i>When the stars in the sky
shine, they start to tell a story</i>
{\ O (rank): I'll tell you}

1150
01:17:46,000 --> 01:17:54,200
<i>Let’s pray that this light
will illuminate the darkness</i>

1151
01:17:58,800 --> 01:18:00,700
Thank you, sir!

1152
01:18:01,400 --> 01:18:05,000
You are too good-natured!

1153
01:18:05,000 --> 01:18:08,900
This scumbag will laugh at
you tomorrow morning!

1154
01:18:08,900 --> 01:18:12,800
That may be true,

1155
01:18:12,800 --> 01:18:15,800
But think about it the other way around.

1156
01:18:16,200 --> 01:18:26,800
<i>From the prison called fate,
people reach for the stars</i>

1157
01:18:28,000 --> 01:18:35,800
<i>Let’s embrace that courage,
that loneliness,</i>

1158
01:18:35,800 --> 01:18:36,800
<i>That pain</i>

1159
01:18:36,800 --> 01:18:46,800
<i>Everything is connected</i>

1160
01:18:46,800 --> 01:18:55,300
<i>There’s a meaning to it all</i>

1161
01:18:55,300 --> 01:19:03,800
<i>I believe in humanity
and all of its resolve</i>

1162
01:19:03,800 --> 01:19:12,300
I can’t see stars or nothin’!
That’s bollocks!

1163
01:19:12,300 --> 01:19:20,800
That’s why...

1164
01:19:20,800 --> 01:19:29,800
<i>I’ll keep on believing</i>

1165
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:35,000
<i>That this gold I’ve passed on</i>

1166
01:19:35,000 --> 01:19:40,200
<i>Will shine one day</i>

1167
01:19:40,200 --> 01:19:45,400
<i>With all of my resolve...</i>

1168
01:19:45,400 --> 01:19:50,600
<i>I will defy fate!</i>

1169
01:19:50,600 --> 01:19:55,800
Inspector.

1170
01:19:55,800 --> 01:19:57,800
I’ll wait for Dio.

1171
01:19:58,800 --> 01:19:59,800
He can still be stopped.

1172
01:20:24,000 --> 01:20:26,000
I heard a bizarre rumour on the streets.

1173
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:31,000
It’s said that a vagabond shattered
a wall with his bare hands.

1174
01:20:31,000 --> 01:20:34,000
And then...

1175
01:20:34,000 --> 01:20:37,000
When the morning sun hit the man,
he turned to ashes and vanished.

1176
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:39,000
It’s the same as what
happened 30 years ago...
{\ O (rank): Yes, I said}

1177
01:20:39,000 --> 01:20:54,000
<i>It’s a wedge driven into
the wasteland of my memory</i>

1178
01:20:54,000 --> 01:20:58,000
<i>At dawn, a blood-red sun
rose over the Atlantic Ocean</i>
{\ O (rank): It's not a lie}

1179
01:20:58,000 --> 01:21:17,000
<i>Full of passion and yearning
for the unknown world</i>
{\ O (spread): This is what I gave to him}

1180
01:21:17,000 --> 01:21:21,000
<i>I crossed the seven seas
with my respected father</i>
{\ O (rank): He is innocent}

1181
01:21:21,000 --> 01:21:21,076
<i>My beloved father, the voices
of my friends, my youth</i>
{\ O (spread): It's one half of your wife.}

1182
01:21:21,076 --> 01:21:21,152
<i>The Stone Mask took
everything away from me</i>
{\ O (spread): Brand-san}

1183
01:21:21,152 --> 01:21:21,228
<i>I swore I’d get revenge,
that I’d take it all back</i>

1184
01:21:21,228 --> 01:21:21,304
<i>Maybe not today, but
there’s always tomorrow</i>
{\ O (spread): This is yours}

1185
01:21:21,304 --> 01:21:21,380
<i>Yes, tomorrow...</i>
{\ O (spread): Please give this ring to me and buy something for your family.}

1186
01:21:21,380 --> 01:21:21,456
“A man is what he thinks
about all day long.”
{\ O (spread): Lord Joster, why did you do that?}

1187
01:21:21,456 --> 01:21:21,532
There’s a saying that goes like that.
{\ O (spread): If I were suffering in poverty}

1188
01:21:21,532 --> 01:21:21,608
The Stone Mask...
{\ O (spread): I would have done the same}

1189
01:21:21,608 --> 01:21:21,684
If I don’t find it, I can’t
recover what I’ve lost.

1190
01:21:21,684 --> 01:21:21,760
I, Dio, was...

1191
01:21:21,760 --> 01:21:21,836
Shit...
{\ O (spread): The stars in the sky are attracted to each other}

1192
01:21:21,836 --> 01:21:21,912
JoJo...

1193
01:21:21,912 --> 01:21:22,000
I see you’ve returned from London—
{\ O (spread): This light will clear the darkness}

1194
01:21:22,000 --> 01:21:26,000
I have the antidote now.

1195
01:21:26,000 --> 01:21:50,500
It’s a shame it had
to come to this, Dio.
{\ O (spread): thank you}

1196
01:21:50,500 --> 01:22:15,000
It truly hurts me.
{\ O (spread): You are too kind}

1197
01:22:15,000 --> 01:22:39,500
Although you might not believe me,
{\ O (spread): This villain is laughing inside}

1198
01:22:39,500 --> 01:23:04,000
Those are my true feelings.
{\ O (spread): Maybe so}

1199
01:23:04,000 --> 01:23:06,000
I understand, JoJo.
{\ O (rank): But think the other way around.}

1200
01:23:06,000 --> 01:23:14,000
You’re honest like that.
{\ O (spread): From the music of destiny, people reach out to the stars}

1201
01:23:14,000 --> 01:23:16,000
Although it’s selfish,
I have a favour to ask—
{\ O (rank): Let's embrace that courage, that loneliness}

1202
01:23:16,000 --> 01:23:21,000
The final one
I will ask of you.
{\ O (spread): Pain is all connected}

1203
01:23:21,000 --> 01:23:23,000
Can you give me more time?

1204
01:23:23,000 --> 01:23:25,000
Time—

1205
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,000
To turn myself in to the police.

1206
01:23:27,000 --> 01:23:34,000
Eh?

1207
01:23:34,000 --> 01:23:36,000
I...

1208
01:23:36,000 --> 01:23:42,400
R-Regret the choices I’ve
made throughout my life.

1209
01:23:42,400 --> 01:23:48,800
Because I was born into squalor...
{\ O (spread): I'm ready to keep believing}

1210
01:23:48,800 --> 01:23:55,200
My ambition was relentless.

1211
01:23:55,200 --> 01:24:01,600
What I did was terrible!
{\ O (spread): I'm waiting for D.}

1212
01:24:01,600 --> 01:24:08,000
I want to repent for my sins!
{\ O (spread): It can still be stopped}

1213
01:24:08,000 --> 01:24:10,000
Don’t believe a word he says!

1214
01:24:10,000 --> 01:24:25,000
I can see from your face that
you’re wondering who I am.

1215
01:24:25,000 --> 01:24:27,000
Allow me to introduce myself!
{\ O (rank): - I heard a strange rumor.}

1216
01:24:27,000 --> 01:24:30,000
I’m Speedwagon, the meddler!

1217
01:24:30,000 --> 01:24:33,400
Growing up in the darkest slums,
{\ O (spread): - He reportedly broke the wall with his bare hands.}

1218
01:24:33,400 --> 01:24:36,800
I’ve met all sorts of horrible
people throughout my life.
{\ O (spread): - And then the man, in the morning sun,}

1219
01:24:36,800 --> 01:24:40,200
So I can tell all I need to know
about a person just from their smell.
{\ O (spread): - It won't fit.}

1220
01:24:40,200 --> 01:24:43,600
This guy reeks!

1221
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:47,000
Worse than vomit!
{\ O (spread): - It's the same as 30 years ago.}

1222
01:24:47,000 --> 01:24:49,000
He was born evil!
{\ O (gap): - Just like back then.}

1223
01:24:49,000 --> 01:24:51,782
Mr. Joestar, you should call
for the police right away.

1224
01:24:51,782 --> 01:24:54,564
This man has confessed already.
{\ O (spread): - A smashed grass fire.}

1225
01:24:54,564 --> 01:24:57,346
Father...
{\ O (spread): - That sunrise over the Atlantic Ocean}

1226
01:24:57,346 --> 01:25:00,128
I’ve heard everything I need to.

1227
01:25:00,128 --> 01:25:02,910
I will return to my bed to rest.

1228
01:25:02,910 --> 01:25:05,692
I don’t want to see my son
being taken away in handcuffs.
{\ O (spread): - I'm fascinated by the world of roads.}

1229
01:25:05,692 --> 01:25:08,474
You won’t succeed in arresting that man...
{\ O (spread): - My respected father,}

1230
01:25:08,474 --> 01:25:11,256
He was born with an innate destiny.
{\ O (spread): - Crossed the seven seas.}

1231
01:25:11,256 --> 01:25:14,040
Silence!
{\ O (spread): - Dear Father and Mother,}

1232
01:25:14,040 --> 01:25:16,880
Come on—

1233
01:25:16,880 --> 01:25:22,512
JoJo, I understand!

1234
01:25:22,512 --> 01:25:28,144
Arrest me.

1235
01:25:28,144 --> 01:25:33,776
But, if it’s not too much to ask;

1236
01:25:33,776 --> 01:25:39,408
