03:05:23,564 --> 03:05:29,256
I would like to think our performance’s
quality is thanks to your support.

2595
03:05:29,256 --> 03:05:34,948
Truly, you’ve made each member of
this performance happy. Thank you.

2596
03:05:34,948 --> 03:05:40,640
From the bottom of my heart,

2597
03:05:40,640 --> 03:05:46,332
Pow.

2598
03:05:46,332 --> 03:05:52,024
MAMORU: From the bottom of the heart, pow!

2599
03:05:52,024 --> 03:05:57,716
Well, I played the role of Jonathan
Joestar, I’m Matsushita Yuya.

2600
03:05:57,716 --> 03:06:03,408
Thank you for today!

2601
03:06:03,408 --> 03:06:09,100
Did you have fun, everyone?!

2602
03:06:09,100 --> 03:06:14,792
The best, hearing this is the best, yeah.

2603
03:06:14,792 --> 03:06:20,484
Uh, right. Really, tomorrow’s
truly the final performance.

2604
03:06:20,484 --> 03:06:26,176
That curtain call will
be the grand finale, too.

2605
03:06:26,176 --> 03:06:31,868
I think that Shotaro will
do perfectly tomorrow.

2606
03:06:31,868 --> 03:06:37,560
I—are you worried?

2607
03:06:37,560 --> 03:06:43,252
Nah, it’s probably okay.

2608
03:06:43,252 --> 03:06:48,944
-I’m worried, so please do the speech instead!

2609
03:06:48,944 --> 03:06:54,636
-He’s—that’s in the past.

2610
03:06:54,636 --> 03:07:00,328
Yeah, no. Anyway I think he’ll be fine.

2611
03:07:00,328 --> 03:07:06,020
I wanted to voice some
personal thoughts here.

2612
03:07:06,020 --> 03:07:11,712
First off, as Mr. Hirose said before,

2613
03:07:11,712 --> 03:07:17,404
It’s been a long road to
arrive at our final performance.

2614
03:07:17,404 --> 03:07:23,096
And I’m relieved that we made it.

2615
03:07:23,096 --> 03:07:28,788
Truly, I’m truly happy to
be on this stage. Thank you!

2616
03:07:28,788 --> 03:07:34,480
Back in February, right?
Opening night was delayed.

2617
03:07:34,480 --> 03:07:40,172
But when we made it to opening day,

2618
03:07:40,172 --> 03:07:45,864
At that curtain call, really, at that time,
the audience cheered and applauded a lot,

2619
03:07:45,864 --> 03:07:51,556
Which has continued up through today.

2620
03:07:51,556 --> 03:07:57,248
Truthfully, at that time, I was feeling, within
me, that we became something unforgettable.

2621
03:07:57,248 --> 03:08:02,940
Yes, that’s right. Truly,
thank you for everything.

2622
03:08:02,940 --> 03:08:08,632
For having supported us up to this point.

2623
03:08:08,632 --> 03:08:14,324
And to Mamo, who supported
me like a partner in this.

2624
03:08:14,324 --> 03:08:20,016
Isn’t it seriously amazing that
he did this role without a double?

2625
03:08:20,016 --> 03:08:25,708
MAMORU: It’s alright.
YUYA: No, it was wonderful.

2626
03:08:25,708 --> 03:08:31,400
Before you even started,
I almost cried when I saw your face.

2627
03:08:31,400 --> 03:08:37,092
Yeah, me too a bit! I got emotional!

2628
03:08:37,092 --> 03:08:42,784
MAMORU: Yes.
YUYA: Sorry, I had to excuse myself.

2629
03:08:42,784 --> 03:08:48,476
Excuse yourself...

2630
03:08:48,476 --> 03:08:54,168
YUYA: It wasn’t because of you or something like that that I left.
MAMORU: I get it.

2631
03:08:54,168 --> 03:08:59,860
Nah, you were really incredible.
Really spectacularly incredible.

2632
03:08:59,860 --> 03:09:05,552
MAMORU: Not at all.
YUYA: No, no, I’m sorry.

2633
03:09:05,552 --> 03:09:11,244
It might be unusual for a performer to say this,
but I truly respect you. Really, you’re wonderful.

2634
03:09:11,244 --> 03:09:16,936
MAMORU: No, no really.
YUYA: I thought he really rejected his humanity.

2635
03:09:16,936 --> 03:09:22,628
You were just that wonderful.

2636
03:09:22,628 --> 03:09:28,320
[INAUDIBLE]

2637
03:09:28,320 --> 03:09:34,012
MAMORU: Thanks.
YUYA: Yes. So then...

2638
03:09:34,012 --> 03:09:39,704
We’re not on the same stage
tonight as we were then, but—

2639
03:09:39,704 --> 03:09:45,396
From the first day of rehearsals until now, he’s
supported me, helped me improve, and encouraged me.

2640
03:09:45,396 --> 03:09:51,088
Shotaro too. I truly believe that without those
two, I would never have achieved this JoJo.

2641
03:09:51,088 --> 03:09:56,780
So, this has been my first time
acting in a double cast performance.

2642
03:09:56,780 --> 03:10:02,472
Thank you everyone in the cast!

2643
03:10:02,472 --> 03:10:08,164
It was wonderful. Thanks!

2644
03:10:08,164 --> 03:10:13,856
And above all, above all, truly,
thank you for being devoted like this!

2645
03:10:13,856 --> 03:10:19,548
Now to everyone at the theatre,

2646
03:10:19,548 --> 03:10:25,240
And everyone watching the stream,
I don’t know where the cameras are but—

2647
03:10:25,240 --> 03:10:31,000
Thank you from the bottom of my heart!
{\ O (spread): JoJo!}

2648
03:10:31,000 --> 03:10:33,000
Thanks!

2649
03:10:33,000 --> 03:10:41,473
I was already so relieved that
I could raise my voice today.

2650
03:10:41,473 --> 03:10:49,946
Yes, and tomorrow Mr. Hirose and I will
be watching the final performance together!

2651
03:10:49,946 --> 03:10:58,419
Everyone, do your best!

2652
03:10:58,419 --> 03:11:06,892
I’ll be giving it my all along with you!

2653
03:11:06,892 --> 03:11:15,365
Everyone, make sure
to—what are you saying?

2654
03:11:15,365 --> 03:11:23,838
I’m doing it! I was
just getting to it, okay?!

2655
03:11:23,838 --> 03:11:32,311
I’m gonna watch it too!

2656
03:11:32,311 --> 03:11:40,784
Yeah, I’ll watch too.

2657
03:11:40,784 --> 03:11:49,257
Pardon me.

2658
03:11:49,257 --> 03:11:57,730
And so, please support everyone
through tomorrow’s final performance!

2659
03:11:57,730 --> 03:12:06,203
Truly, thank you for today!

2660
03:12:06,203 --> 03:12:14,676
{\an8}[TN: Everyone’s muted for about 2 min]

2661
03:12:14,676 --> 03:12:23,149
[INAUDIBLE]

2662
03:12:23,149 --> 03:12:31,622
MAMORU: It’s already over.

2663
03:12:31,622 --> 03:12:40,095
[INAUDIBLE]

2664
03:12:40,095 --> 03:12:48,568
Thank you! Thank you!

2665
03:12:48,568 --> 03:12:57,041
Definitely, please support
tomorrow’s performance too!

2666
03:12:57,041 --> 03:13:05,514
Shotaro, do your best tomorrow!

2667
03:13:05,514 --> 03:13:14,000
MAMORU: Do your best!

2668
03:13:14,000 --> 03:13:16,000
Thank you!

